=A0or his estranged son=E2=80=99s tattoos=C2=A0or whatever, then a=C2=A0thu=
dding transition, then bond stuff. They were fun!Gross left Pimco for Janus=
 in 2014, and kept writing IOs in roughly the same style. Then he retired f=
rom fund management in 2019 and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0just kept writing the IOs? W=
hy not? He no longer has clients, technically, but I suppose his old client=
s still want to know what he has to say about the bond market. Or not, I do=
n=E2=80=99t know, I rarely read the bond-market parts, I assume that what i=
s actually going on is that (1) he still enjoys writing=C2=A0about his pers=
onal life and (2) people still very much enjoy reading about it?As he gets =
further and further removed from active involvement in the bond market, and=
 as his personal life becomes increasingly baroque, the letters keep gettin=
