moves on to how he did his community service in a soup kitchen but was offe=
nded that the food was too good and the customers too well-dressed:Many of =
those requesting vegan were well dressed and apparently not lacking in the =
finer accoutrements of daily life. "We can't discriminate against those who=
 have already been discriminated against," remarked one of the permanent st=
aff. "We can't deny them twice". Ah yes I said to myself =E2=80=93 I know w=
hat you mean.Then a brief pitch for=C2=A0yieldy stocks as a better bet than=
 Treasuries.=C2=A0I do think that if Gross were still employed as a bond ma=
nager and he wrote a seven-paragraph investor letter that devoted two parag=
raphs to his brushes with the law, two paragraphs to what stocks you should=
 buy instead of bonds, and three paragraphs to how soup kitchens are too cu=
shy these days, someone might have gently suggested that he tone it down? E=
ven him, I mean? But now there are no clients and no rules. I can=E2=80=99t=
 wait for next month=E2=80=99s. The man has invented his own literary genre=
; how can you not respect that? In like five years these are going to be 20=
-page Knausgaardian ruminations ending with a single paragraph like =E2=80=
=9CI continue to own some stocks,=E2=80=9D and they are still going to be t=
itled =E2=80=9CInvestment Outlook.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
