y by becoming a public benefit corporation focused on the public benefit of=
 accurately informing its viewers. This feels like it is not going to happe=
n for a lot of reasons, one of them being that Rupert Murdoch owns 41% of t=
he voting power of Fox stock, though that is not the only reason.[2]</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what I like about this proposal is its argume=
nt for=C2=A0<em>why=C2=A0</em>shareholders should vote for it. The argument=
 is not =E2=80=9Cprioritizing truth over money will make more money for sha=
reholders in the long run=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0which is absolutely an ar=
gument that one could make, and which is structurally similar to <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25340495.257884/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
